01:45.280 --> 01:46.240
Did you sleep well?

01:48.240 --> 01:49.080
No.

01:50.760 --> 01:51.600
Orange juice.

02:30.960 --> 02:31.800
Hi.

02:42.120 --> 02:44.640
Someone needs to go grocery shopping.

02:44.720 --> 02:45.560
Hi!

02:47.160 --> 02:49.520
Smells like something died in there.

02:50.560 --> 02:52.360
We're out of cereal.

02:56.200 --> 02:58.080
<i>You look a little down.</i>

02:58.760 --> 02:59.640
Some bread?

03:00.800 --> 03:01.640
No, thanks.

03:06.400 --> 03:08.600
At GPMA, you were always in a foul mood.

03:10.680 --> 03:12.320
But you're actually very joyful.

03:12.400 --> 03:15.240
I guess I wasn't made
for a high-responsibility job.

03:16.200 --> 03:18.440
And I don't drink anymore.

03:20.080 --> 03:23.040
Insurers are so misunderstood.

03:23.120 --> 03:24.240
No one likes us.

03:25.880 --> 03:27.480
You don't care at all, do you?

03:27.560 --> 03:28.680
Of course I do.

03:29.880 --> 03:32.960
But Christmas is in three days
and Patrick hasn't called

03:33.480 --> 03:35.400
to give me his answer.

03:35.480 --> 03:36.480
Christmas.

03:38.320 --> 03:40.720
It's so dull.
I'd rather jump out a window.

03:41.840 --> 03:44.280
We should go to the theater.

03:44.360 --> 03:46.000
Civilized people do that.

03:46.080 --> 03:47.640
I don't care about Christmas.

03:49.200 --> 03:51.320
The point is we'd be together again.

03:52.040 --> 03:53.840
Maybe travel somewhere together.

03:53.920 --> 03:56.120
Traveling is over, Elvira.

03:56.200 --> 03:58.720
People go places,
but they don't travel anymore.

04:00.000 --> 04:02.240
Your Patrick's already moved on.

04:03.960 --> 04:05.200
Schnitzler said,

04:05.280 --> 04:08.800
"It's easier to catch a bird in flight

04:08.880 --> 04:10.800
than love slipping away."

04:11.480 --> 04:12.680
Fuck Schnitzler.

04:16.040 --> 04:17.480
-Is it him?
-No.

04:17.560 --> 04:18.880
But maybe good news.

04:19.400 --> 04:20.320
Gotta go.

04:20.960 --> 04:21.800
Hang on.

04:29.040 --> 04:30.920
-I bought you some clothes.
-But…

04:36.160 --> 04:37.160
Thank you.

04:38.160 --> 04:40.080
We need to buy groceries.

04:41.040 --> 04:42.480
When will the twins be back?

04:45.200 --> 04:47.560
Don't know. I think
they've hooked up with some guys.

04:48.080 --> 04:50.760
We could go to the supermarket.
I'm free this morning.

04:51.640 --> 04:53.080
What's that doing here?

04:55.120 --> 04:56.960
Found one biscuit. Carole?

05:01.200 --> 05:02.400
That's mine.

05:03.920 --> 05:06.360
So now you're hiding food?

05:06.440 --> 05:09.320
I need a snack after swimming.

05:09.400 --> 05:10.960
-It's the holidays.
-What?

05:11.520 --> 05:12.840
It's the holidays.

05:12.920 --> 05:14.440
School ends tonight, Dad.

05:14.520 --> 05:16.600
What parent doesn't know that?

05:17.520 --> 05:20.520
Some of my friends are going skiing.
But us, nothing.

05:21.040 --> 05:23.280
It's gonna be the worst Christmas--

05:24.040 --> 05:24.880
Ever.

05:30.840 --> 05:32.040
Dad?

05:32.680 --> 05:33.520
Dad?

05:38.480 --> 05:39.800
I'm awake now.

05:40.600 --> 05:41.760
Sam, let's go shopping.

05:44.800 --> 05:46.440
I promise you a great Christmas.

05:56.280 --> 05:57.120
Here.

06:16.040 --> 06:16.880
All right.

06:19.520 --> 06:21.320
Maybe put some shoes on.

06:21.400 --> 06:23.280
Take it easy, okay?

06:24.480 --> 06:26.680
I'm not quite ready for shoes yet.

06:34.280 --> 06:36.160
It's amazing.

06:36.920 --> 06:39.080
We can see the baby so clearly.

06:39.160 --> 06:41.040
He looks like my mother.

06:43.440 --> 06:45.760
I know it sounds weird, but it's true.

06:46.680 --> 06:49.680
The baby's a bit small.
But everything's fine.

06:49.760 --> 06:51.440
Just try and gain some weight.

06:52.280 --> 06:55.800
You're starting month seven,
you can afford it.

06:55.880 --> 06:58.000
It's not been seven months.

06:59.240 --> 07:02.200
She's talking weeks of amenorrhea.

07:02.280 --> 07:05.000
Not actual months. I'll explain.

07:06.680 --> 07:08.600
You can get dressed.

07:11.160 --> 07:12.080
Everything's fine.

07:14.440 --> 07:16.840
That heartbeat…

07:18.920 --> 07:20.240
It's something.

07:44.000 --> 07:44.840
Channa.

07:47.440 --> 07:48.680
I love your new style.

07:49.360 --> 07:50.960
This?

07:52.000 --> 07:52.840
Never mind.

07:53.480 --> 07:55.960
So? What do you have for me?

07:58.680 --> 08:01.120
We have a huge problem.

08:01.200 --> 08:04.080
The aluminum factory, our biggest client.

08:04.600 --> 08:06.080
They want to ditch us.

08:06.160 --> 08:09.280
We've spent months negotiating.
The lease is up in a couple of weeks.

08:09.360 --> 08:12.200
If we lose them,
our office will be shut down.

08:12.280 --> 08:14.000
Like we needed that.

08:14.080 --> 08:16.400
If you get them to renew their contract,

08:16.480 --> 08:20.120
it'll give me more ammo to argue
your case with the higher-ups.

08:20.200 --> 08:22.480
What can I do?

08:22.560 --> 08:24.560
-You had good rapport with the manager.
-Yes.

08:25.240 --> 08:26.640
Yes. Mr. Fongarnant.

08:27.920 --> 08:30.240
He's always worked with aluminum.

08:30.320 --> 08:32.800
One divorce, two marriages, three kids.

08:32.880 --> 08:35.360
Well done, Elvira. You're good.

08:35.440 --> 08:38.720
I used to write all this stuff down
in a little book.

08:38.800 --> 08:41.320
Kid names and ages, hobbies.

08:41.400 --> 08:42.320
Where's that book?

08:42.920 --> 08:43.800
At home.

08:44.640 --> 08:45.680
I'll get it back.

08:46.280 --> 08:48.720
I'll be able to buy Christmas presents.

08:48.800 --> 08:52.320
I'm sick of Christmas already.
If Santa was real, I say lock him up.

08:53.840 --> 08:57.080
The law's pretty clear about that.

08:57.160 --> 08:59.280
Entering homes without consent

08:59.360 --> 09:01.920
is punishable by jail or heavy fines.

09:04.040 --> 09:05.520
Little bit of insurer humor there.

09:08.040 --> 09:09.240
I'm counting on you.

09:28.600 --> 09:31.040
-What do you want?
-To speak to Elvira.

09:32.120 --> 09:34.920
-She's not here.
-I know you're hiding her.

09:36.640 --> 09:38.280
She's gone.

09:39.280 --> 09:40.240
I don't know where.

09:48.880 --> 09:49.960
<i>Don't panic!</i>

09:50.040 --> 09:53.160
Nothing special planned
for Christmas Eve dinner?

09:54.720 --> 09:56.320
Dare to be different!

09:57.000 --> 09:59.480
Why not try a recipe

09:59.560 --> 10:02.760
with duck foie gras and pineapple?

10:03.520 --> 10:07.120
With a nice bottle of champagne,
of course.

10:07.200 --> 10:09.520
Let Christmas surprise you!

10:09.600 --> 10:14.920
-Do you need me to push the cart?
-No. I need it for support.

10:21.040 --> 10:22.360
We need cleaning products.

10:22.440 --> 10:25.040
No, that aisle gives me anxiety.

10:25.120 --> 10:26.760
Let's start with what's on sale.

10:30.680 --> 10:31.520
Dad?

10:33.680 --> 10:34.840
It's the other way.

10:34.920 --> 10:36.080
Okay.

10:38.560 --> 10:41.840
Don't miss our foie gras special.
Buy two cans,

10:41.920 --> 10:46.040
and get one free box
of delicious chocolates.

10:58.640 --> 10:59.720
How's the fit?

11:00.280 --> 11:01.120
Good.

11:05.240 --> 11:07.960
-I'll soon be able to pay you back.
-No rush.

11:09.640 --> 11:11.080
Thanks. See you tonight.

11:12.360 --> 11:13.200
See you.

11:14.840 --> 11:16.960
Hello. Fidelity card?

11:21.920 --> 11:24.360
-See ya.
-Don't you have PE?

11:25.640 --> 11:26.800
I have stuff to do.

11:28.880 --> 11:30.440
"Lorenzo!"

11:31.120 --> 11:33.160
-He's my cousin.
-So what?

11:33.240 --> 11:34.960
I've kissed most of mine.

11:35.480 --> 11:37.080
Including Marie-Joelle.

11:38.000 --> 11:39.760
Yeah, but you were eight.

11:40.800 --> 11:43.280
As long as you don't have sex with him,
it's fine.

11:44.520 --> 11:45.360
Shut up.

11:51.880 --> 11:52.720
Thanks.

11:56.400 --> 11:57.600
I'm skipping PE too.

11:58.320 --> 11:59.320
It's overrated.

12:02.920 --> 12:04.480
Do you need a ride home?

12:04.560 --> 12:05.840
My cousin's got a car.

12:06.360 --> 12:07.680
My mom's picking me up.

12:08.960 --> 12:09.800
All right.

12:10.840 --> 12:14.240
People who pay attention to themselves
also pay attention to others.

12:16.240 --> 12:18.640
Is that supposed to be a compliment?

12:19.720 --> 12:22.400
I like what you're wearing. It suits you.

12:22.480 --> 12:23.320
Thanks.

12:25.960 --> 12:27.160
-Hi.
-Hi.

12:29.720 --> 12:31.280
No driver's ed today?

12:54.920 --> 12:56.360
<i>It's on sale!</i>

12:56.440 --> 12:59.520
<i>Swim in an ocean of flavors!</i>

13:00.320 --> 13:02.760
<i>Go for the fish and impress your guests.</i>

13:03.800 --> 13:06.480
<i>Try something new this Christmas.</i>

13:06.560 --> 13:09.760
<i>Invite John Dory to your table.</i>

13:12.320 --> 13:14.200
-You okay?
-Sure.

13:15.800 --> 13:18.120
Fish is full of mercury anyway.

13:20.080 --> 13:22.480
I've never trusted fish, you know?

13:22.560 --> 13:24.040
Nothing that's from the sea.

13:24.920 --> 13:25.760
Jesus Christ.

13:27.920 --> 13:28.760
The sea.

13:34.200 --> 13:35.040
Fuck.

13:41.880 --> 13:44.200
Dad, look at me. Hold onto me.

13:44.880 --> 13:46.680
Hold on.

13:47.600 --> 13:49.880
Yeah. Breathe in.

13:54.720 --> 13:56.400
One more time.

13:56.480 --> 13:58.640
-I'm fine.
-You sure?

13:59.680 --> 14:00.880
It's over.

14:01.520 --> 14:03.080
Hand over the list.

14:03.960 --> 14:04.840
Let's go.

14:06.960 --> 14:07.800
Fuck me.

14:08.360 --> 14:10.480
-What?
-It's what Carole added.

14:11.680 --> 14:13.320
Right.

14:27.600 --> 14:31.240
<i>Buy yourself a present</i>
<i>and please everyone.</i>

14:32.200 --> 14:35.760
<i>This Christmas,</i>
<i>go for some hot new lingerie.</i>

14:35.840 --> 14:36.880
<i>Happy Christmas,</i>

14:36.960 --> 14:38.760
<i>lover boys and lover girls!</i>

14:39.240 --> 14:40.760
<i>Buy one matching set</i>

14:40.840 --> 14:43.320
<i>and get one makeup kit for free.</i>

14:44.040 --> 14:45.640
Excuse us?

14:48.720 --> 14:50.960
Could you point us in the right direction?

14:51.480 --> 14:52.720
It depends.

14:53.840 --> 14:56.440
Here, the ones for light flow.

14:56.520 --> 14:59.360
Here, medium flow.

15:00.560 --> 15:02.640
There, heavy flow. Don't get

15:02.720 --> 15:05.040
the scented ones.
Periods don't actually stink.

15:05.120 --> 15:07.280
It's a myth created to shame women.

15:07.960 --> 15:10.600
But those fucking industrial scents,

15:10.680 --> 15:12.360
now they stink like hell.

15:12.960 --> 15:17.080
The nighttime range is more absorbent.
And of course, tampons.

15:17.160 --> 15:18.240
A friendly warning.

15:18.920 --> 15:22.760
You can't lose your virginity to a tampon.
That's bullshit.

15:22.840 --> 15:27.320
The hymen's actually not
a flimsy little thing. Let's be serious.

15:27.840 --> 15:30.360
And the clitoris is actually
over four inches long.

15:30.440 --> 15:31.280
That's right.

15:31.800 --> 15:34.760
The little bean you can see
is the tip of the iceberg.

15:35.680 --> 15:36.560
Have a nice day.

15:38.440 --> 15:39.280
Have a nice day.

15:52.240 --> 15:53.120
That's weird.

15:54.680 --> 15:56.360
I grew up here.

15:58.560 --> 16:02.680
I used to play here
when Dad was working on Wednesdays.

16:05.520 --> 16:07.360
Why is he selling the store?

16:08.120 --> 16:09.200
We're broke.

16:10.080 --> 16:11.320
It was a failure anyway.

16:11.920 --> 16:15.640
People have phones now.
Photography's pretty much dead.

16:19.280 --> 16:20.920
Do you know what he used to do?

16:22.080 --> 16:22.920
He sold discs.

16:27.400 --> 16:28.240
Look.

16:28.920 --> 16:30.560
I collect tattoo photos.

16:31.320 --> 16:32.760
I'll make a collage,

16:32.840 --> 16:36.480
and it'll look like someone's back.
Like a puzzle. It's for Sam.

16:37.080 --> 16:38.200
He'll love it.

16:40.600 --> 16:43.040
And here, look.

16:44.040 --> 16:45.000
My mother's back.

16:46.040 --> 16:48.760
She had the name
of her first boyfriend tattooed.

16:50.160 --> 16:51.320
My dad's so jealous.

16:54.640 --> 16:55.480
Come on.

16:57.480 --> 16:58.640
Let me show you.

17:10.520 --> 17:11.360
