19:38.000 --> 19:39.320
A few months.

19:41.840 --> 19:43.480
I'll pretend it's still yours.

19:45.120 --> 19:46.760
Thank you.

19:46.840 --> 19:48.360
-You're welcome.
-You're nice.

19:52.240 --> 19:54.320
It does change the total a bit.

19:54.400 --> 19:59.040
I'm alone with three teenagers.

19:59.120 --> 20:00.640
And Christmas coming up…

20:01.200 --> 20:03.240
It's hard, I'm not gonna lie.

20:06.120 --> 20:07.600
My break's in 30 minutes.

20:08.200 --> 20:10.360
Wait for me,
there's something you need to see.

20:11.840 --> 20:15.240
-Like what?
-It'll help save a lot of money.

20:15.320 --> 20:16.800
You'll want to see this.

20:18.920 --> 20:19.760
All right.

20:23.440 --> 20:24.280
Bye.

20:24.360 --> 20:26.440
Everybody in, please.

20:27.200 --> 20:29.440
Remember to drop your stuff.

20:45.440 --> 20:46.960
Virginie! You okay?

21:22.800 --> 21:23.840
What's all this?

21:25.120 --> 21:28.480
There's this stupid thing,
called "stock destruction."

21:29.000 --> 21:32.440
If it's not sold, it's destroyed.
Even if it's still edible.

21:34.000 --> 21:36.720
That's how absurd European directives are.

21:37.560 --> 21:38.840
We could give this out.

21:40.600 --> 21:41.440
Sure.

21:42.280 --> 21:43.720
Take what you want.

21:47.040 --> 21:49.880
Why are you doing all this?

21:50.800 --> 21:54.640
My horoscope said
this was the perfect day to make a friend.

21:55.520 --> 21:57.480
Right.

21:59.120 --> 22:01.080
I look like a homeless man.

22:02.240 --> 22:05.800
-You're pitying me.
-On the contrary, you're quite stylish.

22:08.880 --> 22:12.160
Who'd let you get away?
One should beg to keep you.

22:12.240 --> 22:14.720
I can't believe your wife dumped you.

22:14.800 --> 22:16.880
She didn't.

22:16.960 --> 22:19.840
I asked her to leave and never come back.

22:19.920 --> 22:22.720
She lied to me. A terrible lie, too.

22:22.800 --> 22:24.920
-Completely crazy.
-Really?

22:25.000 --> 22:27.440
You know what? She sent me a letter

22:27.520 --> 22:29.720
asking for a family Christmas.

22:29.800 --> 22:31.280
How dare she! And?

22:32.080 --> 22:33.680
I tore up the letter.

22:33.760 --> 22:37.240
Well done, that's the spirit.

22:37.320 --> 22:40.400
-Why?
-She's trying to keep up appearances.

22:40.480 --> 22:42.760
Out of pride. No love there.

22:43.920 --> 22:46.800
-You think?
-You should despise her.

22:46.880 --> 22:48.880
That's how you deal with it.

22:48.960 --> 22:51.400
Don't give her a chance to hurt you.

22:52.040 --> 22:54.480
You want some advice? Don't call her.

22:56.600 --> 22:57.920
You like pineapple?

23:20.240 --> 23:21.480
Elvira?

23:21.560 --> 23:22.640
Thanks.

23:24.160 --> 23:27.680
-What did he say?
-Nothing. He's looking for you.

23:29.720 --> 23:31.600
It's nice to see you.

23:31.680 --> 23:33.480
This place feels sad without you.

23:34.000 --> 23:38.120
Thanks for the tea, and biscuits.
They're my favorite.

23:38.640 --> 23:40.120
I'm not allowed to have them.

23:42.720 --> 23:44.720
I'm in my purification phase.

23:47.920 --> 23:49.080
I have an idea.

23:55.640 --> 23:56.480
It fits.

23:59.760 --> 24:00.600
Delicious.

24:02.200 --> 24:03.040
Clemence.

24:03.720 --> 24:05.120
I need your help.

24:05.760 --> 24:06.600
Of course.

24:37.440 --> 24:39.520
-Yes?
-Hello, Patrick.

24:39.600 --> 24:40.600
Is this a bad time?

24:41.520 --> 24:43.760
It is, a bit. I'm about to take a nap.

24:43.840 --> 24:46.080
It's been a busy day.

24:46.160 --> 24:47.160
I need help.

24:48.120 --> 24:49.760
My husband's not here.

24:50.440 --> 24:51.400
It'll be quick.

24:52.080 --> 24:52.920
Please.

26:34.640 --> 26:36.400
What did you two talk about?

26:37.480 --> 26:38.640
Well…

26:39.680 --> 26:40.520
Here.

26:41.040 --> 26:44.680
Have you noticed our tap water's
sometimes a bit murky?

26:45.400 --> 26:46.400
Not really.

26:47.440 --> 26:49.000
-No smell?
-No.

26:50.640 --> 26:51.680
To be fair,

26:52.320 --> 26:54.640
I'm not using much water at the moment.

26:57.600 --> 26:58.440
Here.

27:01.000 --> 27:03.240
My husband and I would like
to start a group,

27:03.320 --> 27:06.160
and find out what's wrong
with the water supply.

27:08.760 --> 27:12.480
It's a great idea,
but what does it have to do with me?

27:13.000 --> 27:14.880
I'm interested in your input.

27:15.880 --> 27:18.880
As… a member of our community.

27:20.480 --> 27:21.720
Also…

27:25.920 --> 27:26.960
Also?

27:27.040 --> 27:29.160
Would you mind terribly
if I had some wine?

28:06.720 --> 28:07.840
Mom?

28:20.920 --> 28:22.640
It feels weird saying it.

28:26.120 --> 28:27.240
You scared me.

28:28.360 --> 28:29.600
Say it in Italian.

28:31.240 --> 28:33.480
Speak to me in my mother tongue.

28:34.760 --> 28:37.120
In my dreams, you speak Italian.

28:40.120 --> 28:41.240
I've forgotten how.

28:42.440 --> 28:44.040
You need to try.

28:47.280 --> 28:49.160
And we'll meet halfway.

28:52.360 --> 28:53.200
You see?

29:01.800 --> 29:02.640
Come.

29:15.040 --> 29:15.960
Refill?

29:18.240 --> 29:21.400
Let's talk about it some other time.

29:21.480 --> 29:23.840
I had no sleep last night.

29:24.360 --> 29:25.360
Wait.

29:26.160 --> 29:27.200
I'd like…

29:28.320 --> 29:29.760
I'd like to dance.

29:30.560 --> 29:32.320
Just one dance.

29:32.400 --> 29:36.840
Well… no. I mean, not right now.

29:36.920 --> 29:40.200
I have to nap before the kids get home.

29:40.280 --> 29:41.120
One dance.

29:41.200 --> 29:43.840
Thanks, it's been nice chatting.

29:43.920 --> 29:45.360
Patrick.

29:45.440 --> 29:48.320
You're hurting me a bit, Clemence.

29:48.840 --> 29:50.440
You're squeezing too hard.

29:50.520 --> 29:51.360
I have to try.

29:52.680 --> 29:54.480
Are you all right?

29:55.280 --> 29:56.120
I'm not.

29:57.600 --> 29:58.840
I have something to say.

29:59.440 --> 30:00.440
Yes?

30:00.520 --> 30:01.880
But I don't know what.

30:01.960 --> 30:02.800
You don't?

30:03.760 --> 30:04.880
Something…

30:05.640 --> 30:06.880
Something important.

30:08.280 --> 30:09.560
But I can't get it out.

30:10.720 --> 30:11.560
It's…

30:12.640 --> 30:13.800
It's stuck, right here.

30:14.480 --> 30:15.320
I see.

30:16.600 --> 30:19.800
I totally get it. I get it too, sometimes.

30:19.880 --> 30:22.240
Feels like something lodged there,

30:22.320 --> 30:24.360
like a ball down your throat.

30:24.920 --> 30:26.280
It's painful, isn't it?

30:26.360 --> 30:28.280
It is, very painful.

30:28.360 --> 30:29.480
It feels like…

30:30.320 --> 30:32.760
Like a big egg, stuck and ready to burst.

30:32.840 --> 30:34.240
That's it exactly.

30:34.320 --> 30:36.280
Unfortunately, I'm familiar.

30:40.680 --> 30:41.680
Sit down.

30:42.680 --> 30:45.560
Will you please stay with me
a little while?

30:46.640 --> 30:48.360
I'm having a panic attack.

30:48.440 --> 30:52.240
When it happens to me,
my kids put me through an exercise.

30:52.320 --> 30:53.920
Let me show you.

30:54.000 --> 30:56.640
Breathe in through your nose
and count to four.

30:57.760 --> 30:58.600
Nice and slow.

30:59.760 --> 31:01.880
And let it all out.

31:01.960 --> 31:02.800
Again.

31:15.560 --> 31:16.800
I can't stay.

31:17.600 --> 31:19.560
In case the others come home.

31:22.440 --> 31:24.720
No, no. Don't worry.

31:25.320 --> 31:26.560
We still have time.

31:28.520 --> 31:29.360
Now.

31:31.160 --> 31:32.240
Cook me some pasta.

31:33.360 --> 31:34.200
What?

31:35.600 --> 31:36.960
I want pasta.

31:57.720 --> 31:58.880
What would you like?

32:01.800 --> 32:03.080
Pasta.

32:03.160 --> 32:05.440
With a bit of garlic and olive oil.

32:05.520 --> 32:06.800
What do you want from me?

32:11.400 --> 32:13.400
To spend some time with you.

32:15.360 --> 32:16.880
Mother and son.

32:19.280 --> 32:20.720
I want you to cook for me.

32:23.520 --> 32:26.920
And… I want to hear about my dad.

32:27.680 --> 32:29.040
Who is he?

32:30.280 --> 32:33.840
And then…
I want to tell everyone the truth.

32:34.840 --> 32:38.000
I need my sisters and brother
to know who I am.

32:38.080 --> 32:41.080
All right. We'll just have to wait
for the right time.

32:41.160 --> 32:43.000
It'll never come.

32:43.640 --> 32:46.560
We need to decide when,
or it'll never happen.

32:48.120 --> 32:49.200
I'm not ready.

32:49.280 --> 32:51.840
-In Italian, please.
-I am not ready.

32:54.280 --> 32:57.320
-Let me go.
-Wait. The door's locked.

32:58.240 --> 33:01.480
I'll get it.
You leave through the back door.

33:02.840 --> 33:05.200
Mom, listen to me.

33:06.040 --> 33:09.080
As soon as I call you, you come. Okay?

33:09.760 --> 33:10.760
Right away.

33:11.880 --> 33:13.320
Or I'll tell him everything.

33:24.000 --> 33:24.840
Hello.

33:25.920 --> 33:26.760
Hello.

33:28.040 --> 33:29.720
Is Patrick home?

33:29.800 --> 33:31.640
No, he's out.

33:33.200 --> 33:34.720
Is he?

33:35.880 --> 33:37.960
I'm Jeff, his brother.

33:38.960 --> 33:41.720
I'm Lorenzo. Distant cousin.

33:44.400 --> 33:46.440
I was making pasta.

33:46.520 --> 33:47.520
Want some?

33:48.400 --> 33:50.880
I'm not hungry.

33:54.600 --> 33:56.200
I just broke up with my fiancée.

34:01.120 --> 34:02.120
Look…

34:03.480 --> 34:04.360
Come on in.

34:10.640 --> 34:12.640
A SEASON ON NEPTUNE

34:17.800 --> 34:19.880
Your parents aren't answering.

34:19.960 --> 34:22.000
Any other relative I could call?

34:42.840 --> 34:44.000
-Bye.
-Bye.

34:45.920 --> 34:47.600
You know the principal?

34:47.680 --> 34:48.520
Yes.

34:49.320 --> 34:50.960
He's been at the house.

34:51.560 --> 34:55.120
He's been through a difficult time.
We helped.

34:58.240 --> 35:00.400
I've got snacks waiting for you.

35:00.480 --> 35:02.000
Pierre made waffles.

35:02.080 --> 35:05.080
Thanks for taking care of me.
Thank God you're here.

35:27.680 --> 35:28.520
Thanks.

35:29.320 --> 35:30.600
I just don't get it.

35:32.320 --> 35:34.600
The trip went so well.

35:36.280 --> 35:38.320
Three weeks alone.

35:38.840 --> 35:40.320
Well, with Leo.

35:43.920 --> 35:46.440
In the middle of nowhere.

35:48.240 --> 35:49.840
Just like in the movies.

35:51.080 --> 35:53.720
-<i>And then…</i>
-Thanks.

35:53.800 --> 35:54.720
Take care.

36:03.640 --> 36:07.240
I've asked my mom to babysit Leo tonight.
I'm seeing someone.

36:07.760 --> 36:08.880
Isa, no.

36:09.400 --> 36:11.080
Remember what we said?

36:12.480 --> 36:14.760
We're together, but we're free.

36:18.160 --> 36:19.880
Didn't we just have a great time?

36:19.960 --> 36:23.080
We did. It's fine for three weeks,
not for years.

36:23.960 --> 36:27.640
A year is just a bunch of weeks piled up.

36:28.680 --> 36:30.920
Let me be frank with you, okay?

36:31.800 --> 36:34.120
Don't feel you have to.

36:34.640 --> 36:36.160
I don't admire you.

36:37.520 --> 36:38.600
Say what?

36:38.680 --> 36:39.960
I mean it.

36:40.040 --> 36:42.680
You're the sweetest guy
but I have no admiration for you.

36:43.440 --> 36:46.200
For me to be exclusive, to love

36:46.280 --> 36:48.840
and to fuck the same person every day,
I need that.

36:54.520 --> 36:55.360
Okay.

36:57.160 --> 37:00.160
Sorry. But I did warn you.

37:03.360 --> 37:05.200
I'll leave you alone, then.

37:08.040 --> 37:09.040
You know…

37:10.600 --> 37:14.400
Maybe being sweet is something
worthy of admiration.

37:15.080 --> 37:19.000
Maybe being gentle is worth admiring.

37:19.080 --> 37:20.960
Maybe being safe,

37:22.000 --> 37:23.120
always on time,

37:24.400 --> 37:27.800
being reliable, is worth admiring.

37:29.720 --> 37:30.560
Anyway.

37:31.520 --> 37:33.520
We live in different worlds.

37:34.040 --> 37:38.200
Your world, the one built
on bling, on showing off,

37:38.760 --> 37:40.040
that's clearly not me.

37:44.920 --> 37:46.400
You said that?

37:48.000 --> 37:50.200
All but the last sentence.

37:50.720 --> 37:52.160
I did kick the bin.

37:54.440 --> 37:56.480
She doesn't deserve you.

37:57.760 --> 38:00.400
Elvira's friends are all rotten.

38:02.160 --> 38:03.000
Dad?

38:09.960 --> 38:10.840
Hi.

38:11.840 --> 38:12.680
Good evening.

38:13.640 --> 38:14.480
Where were you?

38:18.120 --> 38:19.760
You weren't answering the phone.

38:27.480 --> 38:30.760
-Virginie fainted at school.
-Really?

38:31.360 --> 38:32.200
Yes.

38:33.000 --> 38:35.280
They tried to call you.

38:36.600 --> 38:39.360
I turned off my phone.

38:40.360 --> 38:41.840
You must be careful.

38:43.080 --> 38:46.680
Virginie's surrounded
by unsettling vibrations.

38:48.200 --> 38:49.440
What does that mean?

38:52.560 --> 38:55.680
She's different from other girls.

38:56.720 --> 38:58.200
She's very sensitive.

39:00.640 --> 39:04.600
It's like she's channeling
those vibrations. Invisible to you,

39:05.720 --> 39:07.040
but very bad for her.

39:08.920 --> 39:10.320
Like a bat?

39:11.040 --> 39:12.040
Exactly.

39:13.640 --> 39:14.720
Like a bat.

39:15.960 --> 39:19.160
She can sense things are going on,
even when you won't tell her.

39:20.040 --> 39:22.360
Sense events you won't mention to her.

39:25.160 --> 39:26.080
Do you understand?

39:26.880 --> 39:28.160
Of course.

39:28.760 --> 39:32.360
When I was a kid, I was just the same.

39:34.480 --> 39:35.320
Like a bat.

39:38.040 --> 39:39.840
You do understand, then.

39:40.400 --> 39:41.240
I do.

39:44.200 --> 39:46.480
I just loved it, really.

39:47.000 --> 39:49.040
I'm actually very impressed.

39:51.480 --> 39:52.320
By what?

39:56.000 --> 39:57.360
The characters.

39:58.520 --> 40:01.960
How you describe stuff, beautifully.
And the plot.

40:02.040 --> 40:05.040
I'm not too sure I understood it all.

40:05.120 --> 40:06.360
But…

40:07.200 --> 40:08.520
The-- Listen.

40:08.600 --> 40:09.680
The characters…

40:10.280 --> 40:12.640
What they're saying,
I've had the same thoughts

40:13.160 --> 40:15.160
but never the words.

40:18.240 --> 40:19.640
That's a bit light.

40:21.920 --> 40:24.200
What did you like about them?

40:24.800 --> 40:26.560
-Say, the narrator.
-The narrator?

40:29.400 --> 40:30.920
Well…

40:32.800 --> 40:34.480
There's this…

40:34.560 --> 40:36.120
His audacity, maybe?

40:36.200 --> 40:37.960
That's exactly it.

40:38.040 --> 40:40.960
The audacity, but more than that.

40:43.280 --> 40:46.080
I liked his ambivalence.

40:48.160 --> 40:50.240
I really liked that.

40:52.600 --> 40:54.760
Very interesting ambivalence.

40:56.480 --> 40:58.720
There's no ambivalence whatsoever.

40:59.360 --> 41:01.720
-No?
-He's very clear about things.

41:01.800 --> 41:04.000
Very sure of his choices.

41:04.080 --> 41:06.560
Being a paradox is not being ambivalent.

41:06.640 --> 41:09.280
-Of course not.
-You're not getting it at all.

41:09.360 --> 41:11.240
-Hi.
-Hi.

41:11.760 --> 41:12.880
Ready?

41:12.960 --> 41:13.920
Let's go.

41:15.640 --> 41:18.320
-Go? Where?
-Is it your business?

41:20.600 --> 41:21.440
You read it too?

41:23.360 --> 41:25.160
-Good, isn't it?
-Yeah.

41:26.200 --> 41:29.120
Does the narrator feel ambivalent to you?

41:29.640 --> 41:32.760
-No, not at all.
-No, right?

41:34.000 --> 41:35.240
Let's go.

41:35.320 --> 41:36.160
See you.

42:04.520 --> 42:05.720
You okay, kitten?

42:08.680 --> 42:12.200
Do you want to eat? I made dinner.

42:12.760 --> 42:15.040
I made chicken and pineapple skewers.

42:17.680 --> 42:19.400
And pineapple cake.

42:20.360 --> 42:23.800
Well, it's really just pineapple
and some biscuits,

42:23.880 --> 42:27.280
and it'll turn into a cake in your belly.

42:29.440 --> 42:31.200
You're not laughing.

42:31.720 --> 42:32.560
No.

42:33.560 --> 42:34.880
I'm not hungry.

42:38.400 --> 42:40.520
-Should I call a doctor?
-No.

42:42.440 --> 42:43.920
I just need to sleep.

42:48.560 --> 42:50.040
Is it Christmas?

42:51.880 --> 42:53.720
Can you please leave?

42:56.200 --> 42:57.040
Sure.

43:03.320 --> 43:05.840
-Would you like some dinner?
-No, thanks.

43:11.320 --> 43:12.160
All right.

43:30.440 --> 43:32.640
-Good evening.
-Good evening.

43:35.160 --> 43:36.240
Are you all right?

43:36.920 --> 43:37.760
Yes.

43:38.960 --> 43:41.720
Sorry, it's been a tough day.

43:43.000 --> 43:44.240
Want to talk about it?

43:45.240 --> 43:46.600
No. Too complicated.

43:49.840 --> 43:51.320
Are those for your kids?

43:52.440 --> 43:53.440
Not at all.

43:57.320 --> 43:59.800
They never replied, so I think it's a no.

44:03.080 --> 44:04.240
What's that doing here?

44:04.920 --> 44:06.280
Are you working again?

44:10.760 --> 44:13.400
Channa gave me a mission.

44:15.000 --> 44:16.360
The aluminum factory.

44:17.320 --> 44:19.640
They're a tough bunch.

44:21.040 --> 44:22.240
We got them, though.

44:25.760 --> 44:26.640
We did.

44:30.440 --> 44:32.080
-So?
-Well.

44:32.720 --> 44:34.440
They want more guarantees.

44:34.520 --> 44:35.640
Do they?

44:37.360 --> 44:38.680
They're threatening us.

44:42.280 --> 44:44.600
-Have you ever been?
-No.

44:44.680 --> 44:47.000
-You'd love it.
-Yeah?

44:47.080 --> 44:49.640
It's so sunny.

45:14.520 --> 45:16.280
I think I failed the mock <i>bac.</i>

45:16.920 --> 45:18.520
Really.

47:39.480 --> 47:41.640
I hear your sister.

47:42.280 --> 47:44.760
We'll all be together.

47:48.040 --> 47:49.200
What's up?

47:49.920 --> 47:50.880
Sit down.

47:51.560 --> 47:53.080
I made pineapple toast.

48:00.080 --> 48:04.120
We've all decided to always
tell each other the truth. Here it is.

48:04.640 --> 48:06.120
Your mom wrote me a letter,

48:07.480 --> 48:10.480
asking for us to spend Christmas together.

48:10.560 --> 48:12.880
I'm obviously against it.

48:14.240 --> 48:15.600
I'm not ready at all.

48:16.320 --> 48:18.880
Seeing Elvira would be

48:18.960 --> 48:20.920
a terrible shock,
especially for Christmas.

48:21.520 --> 48:24.080
There you have it. I wanted to tell you

48:24.160 --> 48:26.920
so we can all decide. Together. Calmly.

48:29.720 --> 48:31.640
I'm not ready either.

48:33.000 --> 48:34.240
Can we vote?

48:35.320 --> 48:37.040
Okay. Let's vote.

48:37.120 --> 48:38.360
I'm voting no.

48:38.960 --> 48:39.800
Me too.

48:40.640 --> 48:41.800
I vote yes.

48:43.960 --> 48:46.040
"Yes"? It's a tie.

48:46.120 --> 48:47.960
How about we flip a coin?

48:48.760 --> 48:49.880
Let's do that.

48:55.240 --> 48:56.560
Tails, she comes.

48:57.520 --> 48:59.240
Heads, she doesn't.

49:00.200 --> 49:01.040
All clear?

49:09.120 --> 49:11.640
On Neptune, winter lasts for 40 years.

49:47.720 --> 49:50.080
Subtitle translation by: Rhys Guillerme
